itemListElement.name: Seattle Seaplane Flight: Cascade Range and Seattle Tour

name: Seattle Seaplane Flight: Cascade Range and Seattle Tour
description: Take to Seattle’s skies on a thrilling 80-minute seaplane ride to the western mountains of the Cascade Range! The unforgettable flight includes a water take-off and landing from Lake Washington plus aerial views of the Cascade Range’s stunning mountain landscape. Glide around the soaring tops of volcanoes and peaks like Mount Index, and then fly above the city of Seattle, looking out for attractions like the Space Needle, Elliot Bay, Husky Stadium and more.

review.name: Best Way to Travel to San Juan Island
review.reviewBody: We flew from Seattle/Renton to Friday Harbor, San Juan Island, WA for a bike riding trip.  This is the best way to see Seattle skyline and all the islands & harbors.  The view was awesome; the staff were great - very helpful and accommodating.  We also traveled between islands using Washington State Ferries which was very convenient (and free for bikers!).

name: Seattle Seaplane Flight: Waterfront Highlights
description: This exciting seaplane tour lets you admire the whole Seattle metropolitan area from a whole new perspective. Soar over downtown Seattle, Puget Sound and Lake Washington on a scenic 20-minute flight offering breathtaking panoramas. See the Space Needle, spot the homes of Microsoft’s Bill Gates and Paul Allen, view the awesome houseboats on Lake Union and more, all with the stunning Olympic Mountains and Mt Rainier as your backdrop.

review.name: Incredible Trip!
review.reviewBody: This was absolutely incredible, highly recommend! The sights were beautiful and it was 100% worth it

itemListElement.name: Seattle Dinner Soiree-A Night On The Town

name: Seattle Dinner Soiree-A Night On The Town
description: Enjoy a progressive 4-course dinner from James Beard award-winning chefs at some of Seattle's top restaurants during this 2-hour walking tour. Experience full-size portions of two appetizers, a main course, and a dessert and get an insider's look at some of the top restaurants in the city. Pair wines and cocktails with a seafood-centric menu while discovering exciting developments in the Seattle food scene.

name: Private Seattle Lakefront Mansion Cruise
description: Please request your reservation as far in advance as possible as we staff based on reservations! Aboard your private Candere you will be in the hands of a professional and in the lap of luxury. A talented bartender and tour guide, your captain will introduce you to Seattle via an intimate boat tour, private for you and your group. Starting in Fremont, you will cruise by boats and floating homes of all sizes, shapes and ages, including the oldest floating home (built in 1907). Cocktail in hand (or "mocktail" for those not enthusiastic about alcohol or too young to imbibe), you will get a great look at UW stadium, and on a clear day, Mt. Rainier will loom beautifully to the south of Lake Washington. As we cruise around Lake Washington we will see hundreds of beautiful waterfront homes. Returning to Lake Union, you are likely to see draw bridges that are nearly 100 years old open up for sailboats and large yachts, Seaplanes taking off and landing, locals enjoying the sunshine.

review.name: Delightful way to spend the afternoon
review.reviewBody: Captain Dylan is charming, knowledgeable, responsive, and accommodating.  The cruise is fun and relaxing.  I am sure it is even more fun in the summer.  Captain Dylan is a delight to deal with and we greatly appreciated the convenience of being dropped off a Duke's restaurant at the end of a Lake Union.  Highly recommend.

name: Seattle City Premier Tour
description: Get to know the beautiful city of Seattle on a 3-hour, sightseeing tour with the best tour guides in the Northwest. Step into our mini coach buses and enjoy a relaxing ride to the city's most popular attractions, including stops at Pioneer Square, the Ballard Locks, and a great city skyline photo opportunity.

review.name: Great overview of the city.
review.reviewBody: We had a late flight after returning from an Alaskan cruise. So we decided on a last minute city tour. Our driver and tour guide Carl was great. He went above and beyond taking us places we wouldn't have ever found on our own. I wish we would have done this pre cruise instead of wandering around for 2 days.

review.name: Seattle in a nutshell
review.reviewBody:
We had a recent trip with a long layover in Seattle. Having never visited the area, we decided to take the opportunity to explore. We found a tour that would fit our tight time frame and also seemed to cover all the highlights we were hoping to see. The tour bus was exactly where/when it told us it’d would be. Our Driver; Carl greeted us by name with a big smile. He was super friendly & extremely knowledgeable of the area. He was clearly proud of his city and wanted to make sure we didn’t miss a thing! 
He also payed close attention to the time & went above and beyond in making sure we made our connecting flight in time! Thank you Carl! Great day!

review.name: Excellent tour
review.reviewBody: Our female driver whose name started with a c was personable, knowledgeable and patient. Great time was had by all aboard

review.name: Great Seattle tour experience.
review.reviewBody: We did our tour on April 5, 2025 and it was a perfect day for a tour.  Our tour guide, Erica did an excellent job.  She was very knowledgeable and informative and we enjoyed the tour immensely.  Thanks Erica for making our Seattle visit memorable!!!

review.name: Fabulous Tour
review.reviewBody: Ken, our tour guide was amazing! He was super informative and funny! A great way to get an overview of Seattle! Highly recommend it!

review.name: Great tour with Ron!
review.reviewBody: Ron was such a fantastic tour guide! I feel I was smiling inside and out the entire time. He has a great balance of being fun and engaging but ensuring we all made the most of our tour (and trip to Seattle!) and take away some real learnings and knowledge. I found his manner light-hearted yet interesting and insightful and he clearly cares deeply about the city which makes a difference. I have saved lots of recommendations and would definitely take another tour with Ron if I get the chance to go back to Seattle. Thank you :)

review.name: Good tour, would have liked more stops
review.reviewBody: Our guide Ron was great, very informative and helpful, offering to take pictures for folks and show us to the restrooms. We had two teen boys with us who were good sports, but the tour is definitely tailored more for adults wanting to hear the history of Seattle. Both my friend and I also would have liked more opportunities to get off the bus and explore more. Also recommend snagging a window seat if you want to be able to see everything the guide points out.

review.name: Discriminación?
review.reviewBody:
El recorrido muy bueno, el guía también, PEEERO! Un detalle que no
me agradó: al regreso el autobús detuvo su marcha en el lugar donde fue la cita de inicio y el fui expresamente se dirigió a mi esposa y a mí para decir que hasta ahí llegaba el recorrido. A ninguna otra persona se lo dijo!! Éramos los únicos extranjeros y eso pareció francamente DISCRIMINATORIO!!!

review.name: Great Tour of Seattle
review.reviewBody: Erica was amazing. She is very personable and knowledgeable about Seattle. The tour went at a nice pace. Erica provided a nice view into the culture.

review.name: Enjoyable & Innformative
review.reviewBody: OMG!!!!!  We had a ball enjoying the informative tour.  We (two of us) had never visited Seattle.  This tour was more than we expected.  Our guide really knew the city and especially historical facts about Seattle.  The three hours ended too soon!

itemListElement.name: The International Exhibition of Sherlock Holmes at Pacific Science Center

name: The International Exhibition of Sherlock Holmes at Pacific Science Center
description:
A Mystery Awaits!

Footprints, spatter patterns and the powers of observation mark the journey through The International Exhibition of Sherlock Holmes at Pacific Science Center October 15, 2016-January 8, 2017. The interactive experience combines science with history and culture to bring to life the historic underpinnings of author Sir Arthur Conan Doyle’s rich and vibrant stories.

Voucher also includes admission to Pacific Science Center's permanent exhibits including the Tropical Butterfly House!

itemListElement.name: Skagit Valley Tulip Festival Day Tour from Seattle

name: Skagit Valley Tulip Festival Day Tour from Seattle
description: Brighten up your spring with a day trip from Seattle to the annual Skagit Valley Tulip Festival, one of the most magnificent floral displays in the US! Admire the vibrant, vast tulip fields on a leisurely stroll, and stop to chat with the tulip growers and purchase some eye-catching flowers. This stunning spectacle is sure to amaze your senses! For lunch, enjoy free time in the charming village of La Conner (1 hour and 15 minutes north) to browse boutiques and galleries, visit a museum or take a nature walk, letting you soak up the idyllic Northwest atmosphere. Your transportation will include admission to the breathtaking gardens at Tulip Valley Farms and Roozengaarde, where you can wander through row after row of rainbow-hued tulips. Enjoy one farm in the morning and one in the afternoon after lunch.

review.name: Very well planned, enjoyable experience!
review.reviewBody: For the weather, the people, and photography practice it is perfect. My time with Customized Tours guiding an easy getaway was simple.  Thanks!

review.name: Beautiful daffodils and tulips
review.reviewBody:
We might be a week too early for the tulips ( only 50% in bloom ) but the daffodils were in full bloom. Definitely worth the drive of 1.5 hr from Seattle. 

Came on a Friday when sky is overcast; the benefit is small crowd and pictures actually turned out very pretty! 

There is not much for food but kids can buy hot cider or chocolates and hot dogs
You can buy flowers : real or artificial at good prices 

PS. Be careful parking on the side of the roads to take pictures of the field - we almost got a ticket , luckily just a lecture from the police 😜

name: Due' Cucina - Capitol Hill
description: For those who've danced through Italian cobblestone streets or daydream and imagine it, Due' Cucina is your culinary teleportation machine. We're the remedy to the pasta woes of today's America, where finding real, made-from-scratch Italian food is a treasure hunt you didn’t sign up for. So, here's to the taste-seeker and those of us who crave genuine Italian soul in every bite. Welcome to Due' Cucina – where Italy finds you.

itemListElement.name: Couth Buzzard Books Espresso Buono Cafe

name: Couth Buzzard Books Espresso Buono Cafe
Pinoyshki Bakery, Cafe & Bar
description: Pinoyshki (formerly Piroshki on 3rd) offers a fusion of Filipino and East European cuisines, including soups, coffees, cakes, and various breakfast, lunch and dinner options. Our Pinoyshki (filipino piroshki) was so popular it was featured on Food Network Diners Drive-ins and Dives. Piroshki, also known as piroshkies or piroshky, are delicious baked turnovers filled with savory meat or vegetable fillings, ideal for snacks or complete meals. At Pinoyshki the piroshki are freshly made multiple times daily by skilled pastry chefs with over 20 years of experience. The store showcases a diverse range of about 30 flavors, from smoked salmon to the much-loved ham and cheese. For special events like birthdays or weddings, their catering menu includes bite-sized piroshki, salads, cookies, and custom-made cakes, adding a unique touch to any celebration.
